<body lang="EN-GB" link="#0563C1" vlink="#954F72">
<div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US">FYI<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Is the SCSC going to have any role in driving delivery of HI publications or is this being driven at the functional level. In case you haven&#8217;t come across it, please see below for more information
 on HI journals.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Thanks!<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Diane<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<div>
<div style="border:none;border-top:solid #E1E1E1 1.0pt;padding:3.0pt 0cm 0cm 0cm">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span lang="EN-US">From:</span></b><span lang="EN-US"> Hatton, Diane
<br>
<b>Sent:</b> 27 February 2020 15:48<br>
<b>To:</b> Cheeks, Matthew &lt;matthew.cheeks@astrazeneca.com&gt;; Venkat, Raghavan &lt;VenkatR@MedImmune.com&gt;; Dunn, Sarah &lt;sarah.dunn@astrazeneca.com&gt;; Ahuja, Sanjeev &lt;sanjeev.ahuja@astrazeneca.com&gt;; Berge, Mark &lt;mark.berge@astrazeneca.com&gt;; Bleckwenn, Nicole &lt;nicole.bleckwenn@astrazeneca.com&gt;;
 Daramola, Lekan &lt;lekan.daramola@astrazeneca.com&gt;; Qu, Limin &lt;limin.qu@astrazeneca.com&gt;; Schmelzer, Albert &lt;albert.schmelzer@astrazeneca.com&gt;<br>
<b>Subject:</b> FYI High Impact Publications <o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Hello Everyone<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US">I have found information on nucleus relating to HI (high impact) publications. There are a few below IF 15 that still qualify as HI that maybe relevant for CCFS.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Eg, iScience, Nature protocols, Trends in Biotechnology (for a review article). More information on publications can be found on the
</span><a href="https://azusgb01--cms.visualforce.com/apex/Main?sname=Intranet&amp;name=IMED-Publications#/">nucleus page</a> &#8211; the HI list can be found under the FAQ section.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">I don&#8217;t know what manuscripts are planned for this year in the different CCFS teams, but for some of them it might be worth considering aiming for a HI journal in the first instance?<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Any suggestions welcome.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Thanks<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Diane<span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
